
Läslig demo

   INFO  A guided primitive walkthrough
    This showcase names Läslig's public primitives directly so you can see
    what they render and when to reach for them.
    Use Läslig for ordinary CLI output, not command parsing or application
    logging.                                                              
    Think of it as the layer between raw Charm styles and your command's
    result text.                                                        


Structured Primitives

  Record
    what: One object or result rendered as labeled facts.
    when: Build metadata, artifact details, environment summaries.
    example: module github.com/evanmschultz/laslig

  KV
    what    Compact aligned configuration or status.
    when    Resolved policy, flags, execution mode.
    format  human
    styled  true

  List
  - Grouped items  DEFAULT 
    when: Packages, tasks, phases, or capabilities that scan better than a table.
  - Badges stay lightweight  READY 
    why: Use a badge when a quick state is enough and a panel would be too heavy.
  - Detail fields add context  LIVE 
    what: Each item can carry labeled facts and still stay list-shaped.

  Table
  ╭─────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │ compare │ prefer when                               │
  │ ────────┼────────────────────────────────────────── │
  │ Table   │ column alignment matters across many rows │
  │ List    │ items are unordered and short             │
  │ Record  │ you are describing one object             │
  ╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯
  Use Table when comparison matters more than prose.

  ╭──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │                                                                  │
  │  Panel                                                           │
  │                                                                  │
  │  Use Panel for rationale, next steps, and larger callouts that   │
  │  should                                                          │
  │  stand apart from the rest of the document.                      │
  │                                                                  │
  │  Panels are stronger than Paragraph and lighter than inventing   │
  │  a custom                                                        │
  │  layout.                                                         │
  │                                                                  │
  ╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯


Rich Text Primitives

  Paragraph
  
  Use Paragraph for readable rationale, release context, and longer help
  text when a Notice or Panel would be too heavy.
  
  Start the rich-text surface here when your CLI needs to explain,
  teach, or provide context.                                      

   SUCCESS  StatusLine keeps one result compact and semantic (When: build ready, cache hit, package passed)

  Markdown
  
  Use Markdown when your CLI already has release notes, changelog text,
  or generated help content to show.
  
  The block below is real terminal-rendered Markdown.

     Release Notes                                                  
                                                                    
    ## Highlights                                                   
                                                                    
    • one renderer                                                  
    • three output surfaces                                         
    • caller-owned logging                                          

  CodeBlock
  
  Use CodeBlock for commands, snippets, generated files, and config
  examples.
  
  The block below shows a Go snippet rendered through Glamour.

  ╭─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │                                                                         │
  │  Go snippet                                                             │
  │                                                                         │
  │                                                                         │
  │      package main                                                       │
  │                                                                         │
  │      import "fmt"                                                       │
  │                                                                         │
  │      func main() {                                                      │
  │          fmt.Println("hello from laslig")                               │
  │      }                                                                  │
  │                                                                         │
  │  Use CodeBlock when code should stay visibly distinct from              │
  │  prose.                                                                 │
  │                                                                         │
  ╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯

  LogBlock
  
  Use LogBlock for selected stderr or log excerpts while the application
  keeps owning logging.
  
  The block below captures real charm/log output and renders it through
  Läslig.                                                              

  ╭──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
  │                                                                  │
  │  Captured charm/log transcript                                   │
  │                                                                  │
  │  INFO demo: boot complete component=cache                        │
  │  WARN demo: retry scheduled after=3s                             │
  │  ERRO demo: dependency missing name=git                          │
  │                                                                  │
  │  Use LogBlock for selected transcripts while the application     │
  │  keeps                                                           │
  │  owning the logger.                                              │
  │                                                                  │
  ╰──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯


Specialized Packages

  gotestout
  
  Use gotestout for Charm-native go test output when a Mage target or
  CLI command should keep owning process control.
  
  The output below shows the same Build, Tests, and Coverage shape this
  repository prints through mage check.                                


